-So in our context a sprint is
a very focused, intense period

00:31:44.370 --> 00:31:46.490
where we have a team of
people coming together

00:31:46.490 --> 00:31:49.230
from different
disciplines and focusing

00:31:49.230 --> 00:31:52.100
on solving a specific
design problem.

00:31:52.100 --> 00:31:56.025
-Too often there's a process
where one group works

00:31:56.025 --> 00:31:58.690
on something, and then they
hand it to the next group,

00:31:58.690 --> 00:32:00.790
and then that group hands
it to the next group.

00:32:00.790 --> 00:32:03.330
And something gets
lost in translation.

00:32:03.330 --> 00:32:05.830
So this is a mechanism where
we can all get together

00:32:05.830 --> 00:32:09.430
on the same page, and you get
much more tangible results much

00:32:09.430 --> 00:32:11.102
more quickly.

00:32:11.102 --> 00:32:15.285
-The ability to kind of leapfrog
the traditional design process

00:32:15.285 --> 00:32:16.965
is incredible.

00:32:16.965 --> 00:32:18.840
-I think a lot of people's
idea of creativity

00:32:18.840 --> 00:32:20.860
is you have this
freedom, you know,

00:32:20.860 --> 00:32:23.650
leaning back in your chair
and just imagining things.

00:32:23.650 --> 00:32:26.150
And it's really not
like that anymore.

00:32:26.150 --> 00:32:27.840
-Watching what was
going on yesterday,

00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:29.065
there was a lot of arguing.

00:32:29.065 --> 00:32:31.042
There was a lot of
dissatisfaction,

00:32:31.042 --> 00:32:33.320
and they had to figure
their way through that.

00:32:33.320 --> 00:32:37.240
And so today they're actually
testing their prototypes

00:32:37.240 --> 00:32:38.802
and changing tack a little bit.

00:32:38.802 --> 00:32:40.260
And that's kind of
the magic of it.

00:32:40.260 --> 00:32:43.730
When you see these transitions
that these teams go through.

00:32:43.730 --> 00:32:45.470
-A lot of what comes
out of sprint week

00:32:45.470 --> 00:32:48.480
is this intangible
camaraderie that

00:32:48.480 --> 00:32:51.070
helps us work better together.

00:32:51.070 --> 00:32:54.010
But the second part
are the projects.

00:32:54.010 --> 00:32:57.245
-What we're trying to do here
is create very high quality

00:32:57.245 --> 00:32:59.945
deliverables that turn
into real products.

00:32:59.945 --> 00:33:02.692
-An actual artifact at
the end that you can then

00:33:02.692 --> 00:33:06.850
take to engineering to build,
or you can take to customers

00:33:06.850 --> 00:33:08.810
to get more feedback on.

00:33:08.810 --> 00:33:11.050
We hope that there will
be a lot of the projects

00:33:11.050 --> 00:33:13.290
that people are working
on that will get picked up

00:33:13.290 --> 00:33:15.430
in some form or another.

00:33:15.430 --> 00:33:17.645
But there's really no losers.

00:33:17.645 --> 00:33:21.350
When you participate in a sprint
you either win or you learn.

