reacting rather than giving you

00:42:45.310 --> 00:42:45.810
feedback.

00:42:45.810 --> 00:42:47.840
You want them to be moving
through the prototype

00:42:47.840 --> 00:42:49.050
as though it was real.

00:42:49.050 --> 00:42:52.730
And the best way to do that
is actually a little nuanced.

00:42:52.730 --> 00:42:55.480
So I'll totally direct you
to check out the blog posts

00:42:55.480 --> 00:42:58.805
for all the detail about
writing those questions.

00:42:58.805 --> 00:42:59.430
AUDIENCE: Cool.

00:42:59.430 --> 00:43:01.870
You guys spoke about two
pretty different scenarios.

00:43:01.870 --> 00:43:03.870
You spoke about
sprinting as individuals,

00:43:03.870 --> 00:43:05.650
