about bigger groups

00:43:05.650 --> 00:43:08.000
and sort of teams that sprint.

00:43:08.000 --> 00:43:11.000
My question is when you have
groups that sprint together,

00:43:11.000 --> 00:43:13.334
do you interfere at all with
the dynamics of that group?

00:43:13.334 --> 00:43:15.791
Because sometimes you have,
you know, really strong voices,

00:43:15.791 --> 00:43:17.599
and really shy voices,
and stuff like that.

00:43:17.599 --> 00:43:19.890
Do you at all interfere with
the dynamics of the group,

00:43:19.890 --> 00:43:21.650
or do you just kind
of let it happen?

00:43:21.650 --> 00:43:24.120
NADYA DIREKOVA: The question
is whether in large groups

00:43:24.120 --> 00:43:25.620
trying to interfere or not?

00:43:25.620 --> 00:43:27.520
That's the role of
the sprint master.

00:43:27.520 --> 00:43:29.170
I don't call it interference.

00:43:29.170 --> 00:43:32.057
I call it leading.

00:43:32.057 --> 00:43:33.640
JAKE KNAPP: We also
want, when there's

00:43:33.640 --> 00:43:35.889
a dynamic about how decisions
are made in the company,

00:43:35.889 --> 00:43:37.646
